T*
(Dyslexia Reader) Tj
T*
T*
(PRIVACY POLICY) Tj
T*
T*
(Last updated: March 20, 2026) Tj
T*
T*
(Dyslexia Reader is a browser extension for Chrome and Edge that provides accessibility) Tj
T*
(reading tools on webpages. This policy explains what information the extension) Tj
T*
(processes, how it is used, and when it is shared.) Tj
T*
T*
(WHAT THE EXTENSION DOES) Tj
T*
T*
(Dyslexia Reader helps users read webpage text more easily through features such as hover) Tj
T*
(dictionary, sentence highlighting with optional text-to-speech, syllable display, text) Tj
T*
(resizing, line and word spacing controls, and AI rewrite of user-selected text.) Tj
T*
T*
(INFORMATION PROCESSED LOCALLY IN YOUR BROWSER) Tj
T*
T*
(When you turn the extension on for a page, Dyslexia Reader may read and modify visible) Tj
T*
(webpage text locally in your browser in order to:) Tj
T*
T*
(- highlight a sentence you select,) Tj
T*
T*
(- read the sentence aloud using the browser's text-to-speech features when that option) Tj
T*
(  is enabled,) Tj
T*
T*
(- show syllable breaks,) Tj
T*
T*
(- change text size, and) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
