(- adjust line spacing and word spacing, and) Tj
T*
T*
(- display interface elements such as tooltips and overlays.) Tj
T*
T*
(This local page processing is used only to provide the extension's reading-support) Tj
T*
(features.) Tj
T*
T*
(INFORMATION STORED ON YOUR DEVICE) Tj
T*
T*
(Dyslexia Reader stores your settings locally using your browser's extension storage.) Tj
T*
(These settings can include:) Tj
T*
T*
(- feature toggles,) Tj
T*
T*
(- text size preferences,) Tj
T*
T*
(- line spacing and word spacing preferences,) Tj
T*
T*
(- text-to-speech settings,) Tj
T*
T*
(- preferred AI model, and) Tj
T*
T*
(- your OpenAI API key, if you choose to enter one.) Tj
T*
T*
(This information is stored locally in your browser and is not sent to the developer.) Tj
T*
T*
(INFORMATION SENT TO THIRD-PARTY SERVICES) Tj
T*
T*
(Dyslexia Reader does not operate its own backend server. When needed for a) Tj
T*
(user-requested feature, the extension sends limited data directly from your browser to) Tj
T*
(the following third-party services:) Tj
T*
T*
(- Free Dictionary API \(`dictionaryapi.dev`\):when hover dictionary is enabled and you) Tj
T*
(  hover over a word, the extension may send that word to retrieve a definition.) Tj
T*
T*
(- OpenAI \(`api.openai.com`\):when you explicitly use the AI rewrite feature, the) Tj
T*
(  extension sends only the text you selected, along with your chosen model setting and) Tj
T*
(  your API key, to OpenAI so the text can be rewritten in simpler language.) Tj
T*
T*
(HOW INFORMATION IS USED) Tj
T*
T*
(The extension uses processed information only to provide the reading-support features) Tj
T*
(requested by the user. The extension is not designed to sell personal data, build) Tj
T*
(advertising profiles, or track browsing for marketing purposes.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
