T*
(HOW INFORMATION IS SHARED) Tj
T*
T*
(Information is shared only when necessary to provide a feature you use:) Tj
T*
T*
(- a hovered word may be sent to the dictionary service for a definition, and) Tj
T*
T*
(- selected text may be sent to OpenAI for AI rewrite when you request that feature.) Tj
T*
T*
(Other than those direct feature-related requests, Dyslexia Reader does not sell or share) Tj
T*
(your data with advertisers, data brokers, or analytics providers.) Tj
T*
T*
(DATA RETENTION) Tj
T*
T*
(The extension stores settings locally until you change them, clear browser extension) Tj
T*
(storage, or uninstall the extension. Data sent to third-party services is subject to) Tj
T*
(those services' own privacy practices and retention policies.) Tj
T*
T*
(SECURITY) Tj
T*
T*
(Dyslexia Reader uses HTTPS requests for external API calls. You should keep your OpenAI) Tj
T*
(API key private and only enter it into copies of the extension you trust.) Tj
T*
T*
(YOUR CHOICES) Tj
T*
T*
(- You can leave the extension turned off on any page.) Tj
T*
T*
(- You can avoid using AI rewrite if you do not want selected text sent to OpenAI.) Tj
T*
T*
(- You can remove your OpenAI API key from the extension settings at any time.) Tj
T*
T*
(- You can uninstall the extension to remove its local storage from your browser.) Tj
T*
T*
(CHILDREN) Tj
T*
T*
(Dyslexia Reader is not directed to children under 13, and the developer does not) Tj
T*
(knowingly collect personal information from children through the extension.) Tj
T*
T*
(CHANGES TO THIS POLICY) Tj
T*
T*
(This privacy policy may be updated from time to time. If material changes are made, the) Tj
T*
(revised version will be posted at the same policy URL with an updated effective date.) Tj
T*
T*
(CONTACT) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
